{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#6240: SFC Playground <style> v-bind does not work in safari ipad when initializing sandbox ",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:26:02.125277+00:00",
  "text": "SFC Playground <style> v-bind does not work in safari ipad when initializing sandbox \n\n### Vue version\n\n3.2.37\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://sfc.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nGo into the sandbox and try pushing the button\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe color of the text changes\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nThe color of the text is not related to v-bind\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nIpad pro IpadOs 15.5 with safari\n```\n\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\ni'm using Ipad pro ipadOS 15.5 with safari. When I go from the vue 3.2 documentation to the link sfc vue v-bind style does not work\r\nBut if you try to change the code, the code starts working. This is most likely an SFC error \r\n\r\nhttps://youtu.be/IXge2SxjxF0",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "browser specific"
  ],
